<br>
<br>
Kaejz <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#564E39><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ucamoman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Camoman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#F4CC10>(7/4/01 12:35:12 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Lozidal</span><hr size=1> Turtle isn't FFA, it's FCFS....meaning first ones there with the people to kill it get it.  <br>
<br>
I pose these questions to you:<br>
<br>
When you say, &quot;I engaged&quot; did you mean &quot;I started kiting&quot;?<br>
<br>
When you say &quot;with my group right behind me&quot; did you mean &quot;they weren't here yet but they were coming&quot;?<br>
<br>
When you say &quot;Another guild comes up and KS's it from us&quot; do you mean &quot;They got there with the number first and pulled it off me while I was kiting&quot;?<br>
<br>
I mean, I personally wasn't part of this, and to my knowledge neither was my guild, but this is pretty common for run-ins with this turtle.  I for one wish he was put in west waste where I can gaurentee half these arguments would never take place.  In the end, I don't know who was right or who was wrong if anyone, but I do know that as he is now, with the ease of the encounter combined with the quality of the loot not to mention placing him into an easily attainable zone (dragon ring here) these arguments are going to continue to take place....best to keep them between guilds and not open them up to the entire server.  Also, before your guild or group or whatever feels you've been ks'd please honestly the questions above and make sure the  answer to none of them is yes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F25><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ukjice.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KJ ICE</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>EC Pimp</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#F4CC10>(7/4/01 6:19:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Lozidal</span><hr size=1>  Engaged meaning attacking and being attacked. Right behind me meaning standing about 5 feet back while I tanked. We had plenty of people there to take care of Lozi, had said other guild not jumped in. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#564E39><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uoakfist.showPublicProfile?language=EN>oakfist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#F4CC10>(7/4/01 9:11:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   no court of public opinion</span><hr size=1> I'm treating this as purely hypothetical, since I know nothing of the incident.<br>
<br>
Posting on the board may get you some sympathy, but it won't fix the problem.<br>
<br>
  &quot;The other guild argues that Lozi is FFA and KSing is a perfectly legal tactic. Discuss.&quot;<br>
<br>
Nothing to discuss.  If you have logs of people saying they are KSing you and that it is perfectly okay, use /petition and /report.  Walking up on someone who has fully engaged a mob and intentionally KSing is a blatant violation of VI's policies.  You should have petitioned as soon as the KS began, and collected as much logging as possible of the other side justifying their intentional KS.<br>
<br>
If you don't have the logs or anything else to back you up, this unfortunately becomes &quot;he said, she said&quot; and all you will get from it is stress.<br>
<br>
<br>
